In light of various comments, I have revised Proto DB1 as follows:

Proto-PROPOSAL DB3 (Vanyel)
(Creates a Rule)
Speaker Must Post Voting Reminder

    No less than 72 hours and no more than 96 hours before the end of a
voting period, the Speaker must post a reminder of the vote, in the form

Proposal 9999 (name-of-the-rule) is currently under vote;  all votes must
be in by Sun, Aug 32, 1999 at 13:70. (87 hours from now)  This proposal
reads as follows:
   Proposal Text.

The Speaker is given some latitude in the exact form of his announcement,
as long as the announcement includes the proposal name, number, and text,
and the date and time it is due.  Violation of this Rule is a Class A
crime.

It is recommended but not required that the Speaker make a similar 
announcement approximately a day before the close of voting.

***End Of Proto


Vanyel

PS Can anyone cc to me a copy of proto DB2 (combining rules)?  I seem to 
have deleted mine.

