Vanyel writes:
>
>Proto-PROPOSAL DB3 (Vanyel)
>(Creates a Rule)
>Speaker Must Post Voting Reminder
>
>    No less than 72 hours and no more than 96 hours before the end of a
>voting period, the Speaker must post a reminder of the vote, in the form
>
I see a problem here: you leave open a 24 hour window to send out this
reminder. What if this window fals in a weekend?

You are curing the weekend problem for the Voters and you introduce it
for the Speaker.

Aprat from that, I am opposed to this idea. I think a Real Agorian doesn't
need such a reminder.


>It is recommended but not required that the Speaker make a similar
>announcement approximately a day before the close of voting.
>
What????? A second reminder? You are really spoiling us.

What about this:

The Speaker will send out a reminder about 24 hours before closing
of the voting period (likely to fall *outside* a weekend), if quorum
has not yet been reached at the time.

I still would vote AGAINST though, as I am a Real Agorian.

Stella?

